'''''Akhali Gazeti''''' (meaning the ''New Newspaper'' in English) is a weekly [[newspaper]] published in [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]. It is based in the city of [[Kutaisi]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Georgia 2014|url=http://www.ned.org/region/eurasia/georgia-2014/|accessdate=9 May 2016|work=National Endowment for Democracy}}</ref> The paper is published on a weekly basis and is owned by Ekaterine Bobokhidze.<ref>{{cite news|title=Who owns regional media|url=http://www.transparency.ge/sites/default/files/post_attachments/Who%20owns%20regional%20media%20-%202014.pdf|accessdate=9 May 2016|work=Transparency|date=2014|page=22}}</ref>
