The '''Constitution of the Cisalpine Republic''' ({{lang-it|Costituzione della Repubblica Cisalpina}}), was the third and final [[constitution]] of the [[Cisalpine Republic]], before being replaced by the [[Constitution of Italy (1802)|Italian Constitution of 1802]]. It came into effect on 7 October 1801, replacing the [[Constitution of the Cisalpine Republic (1798)|former constitution of 1798]].
