{{Infobox company | name = CzechToll | logo = Czechtoll_cmyk.pdf | type = Private Limited company | hq_location_city = [[Prague]] | hq_location_country = [[Czech Republic]] | owner = [[PPF Group]] | website = http://czechtoll.cz/ }}
'''CzechToll s.r.o.''' is a Czech [[private limited company]], part of the [[PPF (company)|PPF Group]], with PPF a.s. holding 100% of its shares.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://czechtoll.cz/|title=CzechToll|website=czechtoll.cz|language=cs-CZ|access-date=2018-04-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mdcr.cz/Media/Media-a-tiskove-zpravy/Novym-provozovatelem-mytneho-systemu-ma-byt-od-rok?lang=en-GB|title=CzechToll and SkyToll shall be the new toll system operator from 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=mdcr.cz|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-04-26}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/czech-toll/consortium-beats-kapsch-in-czech-highway-toll-tender-idUSL8N1RO20H|title=Consortium beats Kapsch in Czech highway toll tender|last=Editorial|first=Reuters|work=U.S.|access-date=2018-04-26|language=en-US}}</ref> CzechToll has been declared the winner of the tender to implement and operate a system for [[electronic toll collection]] in the Czech Republic from 2020 to 2030, alongside the Slovak company SkyToll a.s.
The [[Ministry of Transport (Czech Republic)|Czech Transport Ministry]]’s tender was won by the consortium with a bid of CZK 10.7 billion. CzechToll's bid was CZK 2.7 billion less than the second most favoured bid from [[Kapsch]], which has been operating the toll system in the Czech Republic since 2006. After signing the relevant agreements, CzechToll will be the electronic toll collection system operator in the Czech Republic. SkyToll is the guarantor for the construction and operation of the system within the consortium, and CzechToll has the role of strategic partner, which includes funding the project.<ref name=":0" />
For PPF Group, the participation in the Czech electronic toll tender process was a strategic decision. This is borne out by success so far in a similar tender in [[Germany]], where PPF, with SkyToll as a subcontractor responsible for technical aspects of the project, is now among the finalists bidding to collect tolls on 53,000 kilometres of roads and motorways.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vz24.cz/clanky/vitez-mytneho-v-cr-czechtoll-skytoll-je-ve-finale-tendru-v-srn/|title=Vítěz mýtného v ČR CzechToll/SkyToll je ve finále tendru v SRN {{!}} vz24.cz|last=a.s|first=iVZ CZ,|website=www.vz24.cz|language=cs|access-date=2018-07-13}}</ref>
