{{Infobox station | name = Gotsiridze | type = {{TBILISIMETRO type}} | style = | image = Metro station Gotsiridze.png | image_size = 300 | image_caption = | address = | coordinates = {{coord|41.742519|N|44.784554|E|display=title,inline}} | line = {{TBILISIMETRO-line1}} | other = | structure = Surface-level | platform = [[Side platforms]] | depth = | levels = | tracks = 2 | parking = | bicycle = | baggage_check = | opened = {{date|1966-01-11|mdy}} | closed = | rebuilt = | electrified = | ADA = | code = | owned = [[Tbilisi Metro]] | zone = | smartcardname = | smartcardstatus = | former = | passengers = | pass_year = | pass_percent = | pass_system = | mpassengers = | services = {{s-rail|title=Tbilisi Metro}}{{s-line|system=TBILISIMETRO|line=Akhmeteli-Varketili|previous=Didube|next=Nadzaladevi}} | map_locator = }} {{Akhmeteli-Varketili Line|left}} The '''Gotsiridze''' ({{lang-ka|გოცირიძე}}) is a station on the [[Akhmeteli-Varketili Line]] of the [[Tbilisi Metro]]. It opened on January 11, 1966. It was formerly known as '''Elektrodepo''' ({{lang-ka|ელექტროდეპო}} "(central) electric railway depot"). It was renamed after engineer [[Viktor Gotsiridze]] in 2011.<ref>[http://www.sakrebulo.ge/index.php?lang_id=geo&sec_id=6&info_id=1882 Tbilisi City Assembly]. 2011</ref>
