{{Politics of Benin}}
The '''Star Alliance''' ({{Lang-fr|Alliance Étoile}}) was an oppositional [[political party]] in [[Benin]], formed by the [[Builders and Managers of Freedom and Democracy]], [[The Greens (Benin)|The Greens]] and the [[Union for Democracy and National Solidarity]]. It contested the 1999 and 2003 parliamentary elections.
At the [[Beninese parliamentary election, 2003]], the party won 3 out of 83 seats.
